						<div itemtype="https://schema.org/BlogPosting" itemprop="liveBlogUpdate" itemscope= "itemscope" >
						<div>
							<time itemprop="datePublished" datetime="2025-05-09T18:07:10+05:30"></time>
							<time itemprop="url" content="https://indianexpress.com/article/sports/cricket/dc-vs-pbks-ipl-2025-live-cricket-score-playing-11-punjab-kings-delhi-capitals-today-match-updates-9989423/#tie-lb-20250509180710"></time>
							<span itemscope="itemscope" itemprop="author" itemtype="https://schema.org/Person">
								<meta content="amitkamath" itemprop="name">
							</span>
							<span itemtype="https://schema.org/ImageObject" itemscope="itemscope" itemprop="image">
								<meta itemprop="url" content="https://indianexpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/JANSEN.jpg">
								<meta content="480" itemprop="width">
								<meta content="267" itemprop="height">
							</span>
							<span itemtype="https://schema.org/Organization" itemscope="itemscope" itemprop="publisher">
								<span itemtype="https://schema.org/ImageObject" itemscope="itemscope" itemprop="logo">
									<meta content="https://images.indianexpress.com/2019/11/ienewlogo3_new.png" itemprop="url">
									<meta content="125" itemprop="width">
									<meta content="26" itemprop="height">
								</span>
								<meta content="The Indian Express" itemprop="name">
							</span>
							<meta itemprop="mainEntityOfPage" content="https://indianexpress.com/article/sports/cricket/dc-vs-pbks-ipl-2025-live-cricket-score-playing-11-punjab-kings-delhi-capitals-today-match-updates-9989423/">
							<meta itemprop="dateModified" content="2025-05-09T18:07:10+05:30">
							<meta itemprop="headline" content="IPL 2025 LIVE Updates: Dramatic scenes of Thursday night">
							<meta itemprop="articleBody" content="
Punjab Kings' Marco Jansen is seen wearing a cap in the bus as he leaves with team members after the authorities asked to evacuate the stadium during the Indian Premier League cricket match between Punjab Kings and Delhi Capitals at Himachal Pradesh Cricket Association Stadium in Dharamshala, India, Thursday, May 8, 2025. (AP Photo)


On Thursday night, the IPL game between Punjab Kings and the Delhi Capitals was halted mid-way through the first innings with Punjab batting on 122/1 after 10.1 overs. The game was then halted with the floodlights going off. it happened right when Punjab opener Priyansh Arya -- who scored a swashbuckling 70 off 34 balls -- was dismissed and PBKS captain Shreyas Iyer joined Prabhsimran Singh (who was unbeaten on 50 when the game was halted) out in the middle. Initially, the organisers and BCCI said that there had been a &ldquo;significant technical failure at the HPCA Stadium&rdquo;. After a prolonged delay, the announcement was made: the game was being called off!&nbsp;
As The Indian Express' Devendra Pandey and Venkat Krishna B mentioned in their report "The players from both teams were asked to board their buses and head to the team hotel. The evacuation was so swift that many of the players reached the hotel with their pads still on."
Eventually, after a meeting on Friday, the BCCI made the decision to suspend the IPL 2025 season at least by a week.">
							<div class="lvblg-box">
								<div class="heading-lvblg"><h2>IPL 2025 LIVE Updates: Dramatic scenes of Thursday night</h2></div><div class="body-lvblg"><figure class="image"><img loading="lazy"  src="https://indianexpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/JANSEN.jpg" alt="" >
<figcaption>Punjab Kings' Marco Jansen is seen wearing a cap in the bus as he leaves with team members after the authorities asked to evacuate the stadium during the Indian Premier League cricket match between Punjab Kings and Delhi Capitals at Himachal Pradesh Cricket Association Stadium in Dharamshala, India, Thursday, May 8, 2025. (AP Photo)</figcaption>
</figure>

<p>On Thursday night, the IPL game between Punjab Kings and the Delhi Capitals was halted mid-way through the first innings with Punjab batting on 122/1 after 10.1 overs. The game was then halted with the floodlights going off. it happened right when Punjab opener Priyansh Arya -- who scored a swashbuckling 70 off 34 balls -- was dismissed and PBKS captain Shreyas Iyer joined Prabhsimran Singh (who was unbeaten on 50 when the game was halted) out in the middle. Initially, the organisers and BCCI said that there had been a &ldquo;significant technical failure at the HPCA Stadium&rdquo;. After a prolonged delay, the announcement was made: the game was being called off!&nbsp;</p>
<p>As The Indian Express' Devendra Pandey and Venkat Krishna B <a href="https://indianexpress.com/article/sports/ipl/ipl-bcci-waits-for-government-advice-ready-with-plan-b-9991718/"  class="" rel="noopener" target="_blank">mentioned in their report</a> "The players from both teams were asked to board their buses and head to the team hotel. The evacuation was so swift that many of the players reached the hotel with their pads still on."</p>
<p>Eventually, after a meeting on Friday, the BCCI made the decision to suspend the IPL 2025 season at least by a week.</p></div>
							</div>
						</div></div>
