							<meta itemprop="mainEntityOfPage" content="https://indianexpress.com/article/sports/cricket/dc-vs-pbks-ipl-2025-live-cricket-score-playing-11-punjab-kings-delhi-capitals-today-match-updates-9989423/">
							<meta itemprop="dateModified" content="2025-05-09T01:33:44+05:30">
							<meta itemprop="headline" content="PBKS vs DC LIVE Score, IPL 2025: What's next for IPL?">
							<meta itemprop="articleBody" content="After IPL 2025 game between Punjab Kings and Delhi Capitals was abandoned mid-way, the Board of Control for Cricket in India said it was "ready with a Plan B" and awaiting "government advice", report The Indian Express' Devendra Pandey and Venkata Krishna B.
Their report, published late on Thursday night on The Indian Express, said: "The unprecedented blackout on the western front on Thursday cast a long shadow on the Indian Premier League. Around 9.35 pm, the match between Punjab Kings and Delhi Capitals in Dharamsala, about 90 km from Pathankot which saw aerial attacks from across the border, was called off after 10.1 overs. Then, the BCCI went into a huddle to decide the future of the tournament.
'We are monitoring the situation, seeking the Government's advice, and will take the final decision on the IPL tomorrow. The situation is changing day by day. We will do whatever we are told and inform all stakeholders. At the moment, our priority is the safety of all players, fans and stakeholders,&rdquo; BCCI vice-president Rajeev Shukla told The Indian Express.
READ MORE">
							<div class="lvblg-box">
								<div class="heading-lvblg"><h2>PBKS vs DC LIVE Score, IPL 2025: What's next for IPL?</h2></div><div class="body-lvblg"><p>After IPL 2025 game between Punjab Kings and Delhi Capitals was abandoned mid-way, the Board of Control for Cricket in India said it was "ready with a Plan B" and awaiting "government advice", report The Indian Express' <a href="https://indianexpress.com/profile/author/devendra-pandey/"  class="" rel="noopener" target="_blank">Devendra Pandey</a> and <a href="https://indianexpress.com/profile/author/venkata-krishna-b/"  class="" rel="noopener" target="_blank">Venkata Krishna B</a>.</p>
<p>Their report, published late on Thursday night on The Indian Express, said: "The unprecedented blackout on the western front on Thursday cast a long shadow on the Indian Premier League. Around 9.35 pm, the match between Punjab Kings and Delhi Capitals in Dharamsala, about 90 km from Pathankot which saw aerial attacks from across the border, was called off after 10.1 overs. Then, the BCCI went into a huddle to decide the future of the tournament.</p>
<p>'We are monitoring the situation, seeking the Government's advice, and will take the final decision on the IPL tomorrow. The situation is changing day by day. We will do whatever we are told and inform all stakeholders. At the moment, our priority is the safety of all players, fans and stakeholders,&rdquo; BCCI vice-president Rajeev Shukla told The Indian Express.</p>
<p><a href="https://indianexpress.com/article/sports/ipl/ipl-bcci-waits-for-government-advice-ready-with-plan-b-9991718/" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><em><strong>READ MORE</strong></em></span></a></p></div>
							</div>
						</div></div>
