<div class="brdr20 lowlighted" id="tie-lb-20250508231147" data-timeframe="20250508231147"><div class="comment-body-live " id="lb-1011801"><div class="The game between the Punjab Kings and Delhi Capitals was abandoned after 10.1 overs. While the BCCI said that there was a 'power outage caused by a significant technical failure in the area which caused one of the light towers to switch off', IPL Chairman Arun Dhumal told news agency IANS that the PBKS vs DC match was 'called off as a precautionary measure, based on the red alert issued in Jammu'.&amp;nbsp;\n\nThe fans at the HPCA Stadium were evacuated after the game was abandoned.&amp;nbsp;\n\n&lt;img src=&quot;https:\/\/indianexpress.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/05\/AP25128586813461.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;800&quot; height=&quot;534&quot; \/&gt;\nAn official asks the photographers to evacuate after the Indian Premier League cricket match between Punjab Kings and Delhi Capitals was stopped at Himachal Pradesh Cricket Association Stadium in Dharamshala, India, Thursday, May 8, 2025. (AP Photo)\n\n\n&lt;img src=&quot;https:\/\/indianexpress.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/05\/AP25128588722547.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;750&quot; height=&quot;500&quot; \/&gt;\nWorkers leave the ground after the authorities asked to evacuate the stadium during the Indian Premier League cricket match between Punjab Kings and Delhi Capitals at Himachal Pradesh Cricket Association Stadium in Dharamshala, India, Thursday, May 8, 2025. (AP Photo)\n\n\n&lt;img src=&quot;https:\/\/indianexpress.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/05\/AP25128590418885.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;750&quot; height=&quot;500&quot; \/&gt;\nSpectators leave the stands after the authorities asked to evacuate the stadium during the Indian Premier League cricket match between Punjab Kings and Delhi Capitals at Himachal Pradesh Cricket Association Stadium in Dharamshala, India, Thursday, May 8, 2025. (AP Photo)\n" id="lbcontentbody"></div><div class="lvblg-box-shr">
