						<div itemtype="https://schema.org/BlogPosting" itemprop="liveBlogUpdate" itemscope= "itemscope" >
						<div>
							<time itemprop="datePublished" datetime="2025-05-08T20:48:45+05:30"></time>
							<time itemprop="url" content="https://indianexpress.com/article/sports/cricket/dc-vs-pbks-ipl-2025-live-cricket-score-playing-11-punjab-kings-delhi-capitals-today-match-updates-9989423/#tie-lb-20250508204845"></time>
							<span itemscope="itemscope" itemprop="author" itemtype="https://schema.org/Person">
								<meta content="amitkamath" itemprop="name">
							</span>
							<span itemtype="https://schema.org/ImageObject" itemscope="itemscope" itemprop="image">
								<meta itemprop="url" content="https://images.indianexpress.com/2025/05/PBKS-VS-DC-EVACUATION.jpg">
								<meta content="480" itemprop="width">
								<meta content="267" itemprop="height">
							</span>
							<span itemtype="https://schema.org/Organization" itemscope="itemscope" itemprop="publisher">
								<span itemtype="https://schema.org/ImageObject" itemscope="itemscope" itemprop="logo">
									<meta content="https://images.indianexpress.com/2019/11/ienewlogo3_new.png" itemprop="url">
									<meta content="125" itemprop="width">
									<meta content="26" itemprop="height">
								</span>
								<meta content="The Indian Express" itemprop="name">
							</span>
							<meta itemprop="mainEntityOfPage" content="https://indianexpress.com/article/sports/cricket/dc-vs-pbks-ipl-2025-live-cricket-score-playing-11-punjab-kings-delhi-capitals-today-match-updates-9989423/">
							<meta itemprop="dateModified" content="2025-05-08T20:48:45+05:30">
							<meta itemprop="headline" content="PBKS vs DC LIVE Score, IPL 2025: After 3 overs, Punjab Kings are 32/0">
							<meta itemprop="articleBody" content="After the first two overs saw Priyansh Arya going for some hits to the fence, we have Prabhsimran Singh taking on Mitchell Starc: he hits the Australian for a boundary on the first ball on the legside, with a casual flick off his pads. Starc responds with a typical fast bowler's reply: a bouncer straight fast his eyeline.&nbsp;
Two dot balls after the boundary on the first ball. And then, Singh gets an inside edge while going for a drive on the fourth ball, and the ball flies to the boundary past the stumps! Lucky there for the batter.&nbsp;
Starc responds to this four with a guided bouncer that Singh just about fends off! Singh responds to that yorker by finally getting a drive right! Three boundaries in that over! And we have 12&nbsp;runs coming off that second over from Starc!&nbsp;">
							<div class="lvblg-box">
								<div class="heading-lvblg"><h2>PBKS vs DC LIVE Score, IPL 2025: After 3 overs, Punjab Kings are 32/0</h2></div><div class="body-lvblg"><p>After the first two overs saw Priyansh Arya going for some hits to the fence, we have Prabhsimran Singh taking on Mitchell Starc: he hits the Australian for a boundary on the first ball on the legside, with a casual flick off his pads. Starc responds with a typical fast bowler's reply: a bouncer straight fast his eyeline.&nbsp;</p>
<p>Two dot balls after the boundary on the first ball. And then, Singh gets an inside edge while going for a drive on the fourth ball, and the ball flies to the boundary past the stumps! Lucky there for the batter.&nbsp;</p>
<p>Starc responds to this four with a guided bouncer that Singh just about fends off! Singh responds to that yorker by finally getting a drive right! Three boundaries in that over! And we have 12&nbsp;runs coming off that second over from Starc!&nbsp;</p></div>
							</div>
						</div></div>
						<div class="clear"></div>
					</div>
					<div class="clear"></div>
				</div>
<div class="brdr20 lowlighted" id="tie-lb-20250508204333" data-timeframe="20250508204333"><div class="comment-body-live " id="lb-1011786"><div class="Chameera comes on and beats Priyansh Arya for line on the first ball!&amp;nbsp; Arya responds with a single on the next ball. And after another single on ball three, Arya is back at the crease. On the fourth ball, he's beaten once again!&amp;nbsp;\nHe responds this time, by walking across the stumps and flicking the ball away to deep backward square leg, where it's kept in bounds by the fielder. And just when we think the over is over, we have a no ball for overstepping.\nWe would have had just four runs from that over if that no ball wasn't bowled. But Arya hits the free hit ball over the fielders in the circle on the off side for a boundary.&amp;nbsp;" id="lbcontentbody"></div><div class="lvblg-box-shr">
							<div class="ieo-datetime">
								<span>20:43 (IST)</span><span>08 May 2025</span></div>
