<div class="brdr20 lowlighted" id="tie-lb-20250508201654" data-timeframe="20250508201654"><div class="comment-body-live " id="lb-1011782"><div class="So the Delhi Capitals will bowl first after a lengthy delay at Dharamsala.&amp;nbsp;Shreyas Iyer has won the toss and opted to bat first.&amp;nbsp;\nShreyas Iyer explains his decision to bat first by saying: &quot;We'll bat first considering the outfield. If you see the last game, the way our openers started and other batters capitalising, that gives us a fair point to come and bat first. If you see the trend in IPL, the players who are in form and win you matches win you the championship. That's a great motivating factor. The team is in high spirits. It's important we tick the boxes right. You got to stick to your routines. We are going with the same batting line-up.&quot;\n\nAxar Patel, Delhi captain, said they would have fielded first because of the weather. He points that the chasing team will have it easier even if there are delays.&amp;nbsp;\n&quot;The wicket will remain the same. It's a long tournament and it's important to be positive,&quot; Axar says before revealign that today Madhav Tiwari comes in for Vipraj Nigam in the playing XI.&amp;nbsp;" id="lbcontentbody"></div><div class="lvblg-box-shr">
