							<span itemtype="https://schema.org/Organization" itemscope="itemscope" itemprop="publisher">
								<span itemtype="https://schema.org/ImageObject" itemscope="itemscope" itemprop="logo">
									<meta content="https://images.indianexpress.com/2019/11/ienewlogo3_new.png" itemprop="url">
									<meta content="125" itemprop="width">
									<meta content="26" itemprop="height">
								</span>
								<meta content="The Indian Express" itemprop="name">
							</span>
							<meta itemprop="mainEntityOfPage" content="https://indianexpress.com/article/sports/cricket/dc-vs-pbks-ipl-2025-live-cricket-score-playing-11-punjab-kings-delhi-capitals-today-match-updates-9989423/">
							<meta itemprop="dateModified" content="2025-05-08T20:24:09+05:30">
							<meta itemprop="headline" content="PBKS vs DC LIVE Score, IPL 2025: Punjab Kings wins toss">
							<meta itemprop="articleBody" content="So the Delhi Capitals will bowl first after a lengthy delay at Dharamsala.&nbsp;Shreyas Iyer has won the toss and opted to bat first.&nbsp;
Shreyas Iyer explains his decision to bat first by saying: "We'll bat first considering the outfield. If you see the last game, the way our openers started and other batters capitalising, that gives us a fair point to come and bat first. If you see the trend in IPL, the players who are in form and win you matches win you the championship. That's a great motivating factor. The team is in high spirits. It's important we tick the boxes right. You got to stick to your routines. We are going with the same batting line-up."

Axar Patel, Delhi captain, said they would have fielded first because of the weather. He points that the chasing team will have it easier even if there are delays.&nbsp;
"The wicket will remain the same. It's a long tournament and it's important to be positive," Axar says before revealign that today Madhav Tiwari comes in for Vipraj Nigam in the playing XI.&nbsp;">
							<div class="lvblg-box">
								<div class="heading-lvblg"><h2>PBKS vs DC LIVE Score, IPL 2025: Punjab Kings wins toss</h2></div><div class="body-lvblg"><p>So the Delhi Capitals will bowl first after a lengthy delay at Dharamsala.&nbsp;Shreyas Iyer has won the toss and opted to bat first.&nbsp;</p>
<p>Shreyas Iyer explains his decision to bat first by saying: "We'll bat first considering the outfield. If you see the last game, the way our openers started and other batters capitalising, that gives us a fair point to come and bat first. If you see the trend in IPL, the players who are in form and win you matches win you the championship. That's a great motivating factor. The team is in high spirits. It's important we tick the boxes right. You got to stick to your routines. We are going with the same batting line-up."</p>

<p>Axar Patel, Delhi captain, said they would have fielded first because of the weather. He points that the chasing team will have it easier even if there are delays.&nbsp;</p>
<p>"The wicket will remain the same. It's a long tournament and it's important to be positive," Axar says before revealign that today Madhav Tiwari comes in for Vipraj Nigam in the playing XI.&nbsp;</p></div>
							</div>
						</div></div>
						<div class="clear"></div>
					</div>
					<div class="clear"></div>
				</div>
<div class="brdr20 lowlighted" id="tie-lb-20250508200913" data-timeframe="20250508200913"><div class="comment-body-live " id="lb-1011781"><div class="So the rains have gone away and the umpires have decided after the ground inspection that the toss will happen at 8.15. The game will start at 8.30 pm.&amp;nbsp;And despite the delay, we will have a full 20 overs game!&amp;nbsp;" id="lbcontentbody"></div><div class="lvblg-box-shr">
