								<meta content="The Indian Express" itemprop="name">
							</span>
							<meta itemprop="mainEntityOfPage" content="https://indianexpress.com/article/sports/cricket/dc-vs-pbks-ipl-2025-live-cricket-score-playing-11-punjab-kings-delhi-capitals-today-match-updates-9989423/">
							<meta itemprop="dateModified" content="2025-05-08T19:58:51+05:30">
							<meta itemprop="headline" content="PBKS vs DC LIVE Score, IPL 2025: Mitchell Starc speaks">
							<meta itemprop="articleBody" content="As we are in a hold pattern with a ground inspection coming up shortly, we have Delhi's Mitchell Starc doing an interview with the host broadcaster.&nbsp;
The Australian is asked about the challenges of playing the IPL.
"You got all the best players in one spot, it&rsquo;s pretty relentless at times with all the travel and play. One of those days where you compartmentalize and get on with the job. Be attacking - that&rsquo;s been my role in many formats for many times. I try and be aggressive, swing the ball and make inroads. Try and adapt to conditions as quickly as we can. With the impact player rule, you have to try and think outside the box and think a step ahead. If it&rsquo;s not swinging you need to find different ways to be effective. As bowlers collectively, people have found that, some have done it better than others," he says.&nbsp;
Then, talking about the art of bowling yorkers, Starc says: "Comes down to execution, some days it&rsquo;s going to work and some days it isn&rsquo;t. Some days you&rsquo;re going to bowl an over and get the team over the line and some days the batter is going to get you. Been around for long enough to be a goldfish really, think about the next game really quickly. Sometimes you&rsquo;re going to miss and sometimes you&rsquo;re going to hit six in a row. Unfortunately it&rsquo;s not going to happen every time"">
							<div class="lvblg-box">
								<div class="heading-lvblg"><h2>PBKS vs DC LIVE Score, IPL 2025: Mitchell Starc speaks</h2></div><div class="body-lvblg"><p>As we are in a hold pattern with a ground inspection coming up shortly, we have Delhi's Mitchell Starc doing an interview with the host broadcaster.&nbsp;</p>
<p>The Australian is asked about the challenges of playing the IPL.</p>
<p>"You got all the best players in one spot, it&rsquo;s pretty relentless at times with all the travel and play. One of those days where you compartmentalize and get on with the job. Be attacking - that&rsquo;s been my role in many formats for many times. I try and be aggressive, swing the ball and make inroads. Try and adapt to conditions as quickly as we can. With the impact player rule, you have to try and think outside the box and think a step ahead. If it&rsquo;s not swinging you need to find different ways to be effective. As bowlers collectively, people have found that, some have done it better than others," he says.&nbsp;</p>
<p>Then, talking about the art of bowling yorkers, Starc says: "Comes down to execution, some days it&rsquo;s going to work and some days it isn&rsquo;t. Some days you&rsquo;re going to bowl an over and get the team over the line and some days the batter is going to get you. Been around for long enough to be a goldfish really, think about the next game really quickly. Sometimes you&rsquo;re going to miss and sometimes you&rsquo;re going to hit six in a row. Unfortunately it&rsquo;s not going to happen every time"</p></div>
							</div>
						</div></div>
						<div class="clear"></div>
					</div>
					<div class="clear"></div>
				</div>
<div class="brdr20 lowlighted" id="tie-lb-20250508195630" data-timeframe="20250508195630"><div class="comment-body-live " id="lb-1011779"><div class="So we have the usualy pre-match rituals being done in the middle by players from both sides. Delhi Capitals' pacve spearhead, Mitchell Starc, is spotted marking his run up with paint. And Punjab Kings captain Shreyas Iyer is doing his visualising in front of the stumps on the22-yeard strip that is finally visible now after that blue cover is taken off! Kuldeep Yadav is turning his arm at one corner of the ground.&amp;nbsp;\nMeanwhile, most of the Delhi players including Faf du Plessis and KL Rahul are playing a game of keey-uppies with the football. It seems like the players who are having too much fun in this pursuit, because the player who drops the ball, gets flicked on the forehead by the others players playing. KL Rahul getting his fair share of forehead flicks from teammates, but he's grinning from ear to ear!&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;" id="lbcontentbody"></div><div class="lvblg-box-shr">
							<div class="ieo-datetime">
								<span>19:56 (IST)</span><span>08 May 2025</span></div>
