<div class="brdr20 lowlighted" id="tie-lb-20250508192232" data-timeframe="20250508192232"><div class="comment-body-live " id="lb-1011775"><div class="In an interview with IPL broadcaster JioHotstar, Punjab Kings Shreyas Iyer opened up about the first season of the Indian Premier League in 2008 when he was just 14 years of age and was a ball boy at all the Mumbai Indians games at the Wankhede Stadium.\n&quot;I used to play for the U14 Mumbai team and we got the chance to be ball boys for games. I was one of the lucky ones. I got an opportunity to meet all players around the team dugouts. I used to be reserved and shy back then, so I was very hesitant to approach players. But I used to see my friends approaching players. The first player I really met and interacted with was Ross Taylor, who used to be one of my favourites. &amp;nbsp;I approached him and said, 'Sir, I am a big fan of yours.' This was during the RCB vs Mumbai Indians game. He was very sweet. Back then we used to ask for bat or gloves from big players. But I was so shy, I could not ask for it!&quot;&amp;nbsp;\nHe added: &quot;There was another incident. In one game, Irfan Pathan was fielding at long on and sat next to us. He asked us 'mazaa aa raha hai?' We said we loved talking to him. That experience stands out for me.&quot; &amp;nbsp;" id="lbcontentbody"></div><div class="lvblg-box-shr">
