								<meta content="267" itemprop="height">
							</span>
							<span itemtype="https://schema.org/Organization" itemscope="itemscope" itemprop="publisher">
								<span itemtype="https://schema.org/ImageObject" itemscope="itemscope" itemprop="logo">
									<meta content="https://images.indianexpress.com/2019/11/ienewlogo3_new.png" itemprop="url">
									<meta content="125" itemprop="width">
									<meta content="26" itemprop="height">
								</span>
								<meta content="The Indian Express" itemprop="name">
							</span>
							<meta itemprop="mainEntityOfPage" content="https://indianexpress.com/article/sports/cricket/dc-vs-pbks-ipl-2025-live-cricket-score-playing-11-punjab-kings-delhi-capitals-today-match-updates-9989423/">
							<meta itemprop="dateModified" content="2025-05-08T19:22:32+05:30">
							<meta itemprop="headline" content="PBKS vs DC LIVE Score, IPL 2025: Shreyas Iyer as a ball boy">
							<meta itemprop="articleBody" content="In an interview with IPL broadcaster JioHotstar, Punjab Kings Shreyas Iyer opened up about the first season of the Indian Premier League in 2008 when he was just 14 years of age and was a ball boy at all the Mumbai Indians games at the Wankhede Stadium.
"I used to play for the U14 Mumbai team and we got the chance to be ball boys for games. I was one of the lucky ones. I got an opportunity to meet all players around the team dugouts. I used to be reserved and shy back then, so I was very hesitant to approach players. But I used to see my friends approaching players. The first player I really met and interacted with was Ross Taylor, who used to be one of my favourites. &nbsp;I approached him and said, 'Sir, I am a big fan of yours.' This was during the RCB vs Mumbai Indians game. He was very sweet. Back then we used to ask for bat or gloves from big players. But I was so shy, I could not ask for it!"&nbsp;
He added: "There was another incident. In one game, Irfan Pathan was fielding at long on and sat next to us. He asked us 'mazaa aa raha hai?' We said we loved talking to him. That experience stands out for me." &nbsp;">
							<div class="lvblg-box">
								<div class="heading-lvblg"><h2>PBKS vs DC LIVE Score, IPL 2025: Shreyas Iyer as a ball boy</h2></div><div class="body-lvblg"><p>In an interview with IPL broadcaster JioHotstar, Punjab Kings Shreyas Iyer opened up about the first season of the Indian Premier League in 2008 when he was just 14 years of age and was a ball boy at all the Mumbai Indians games at the Wankhede Stadium.</p>
<p>"I used to play for the U14 Mumbai team and we got the chance to be ball boys for games. I was one of the lucky ones. I got an opportunity to meet all players around the team dugouts. I used to be reserved and shy back then, so I was very hesitant to approach players. But I used to see my friends approaching players. The first player I really met and interacted with was Ross Taylor, who used to be one of my favourites. &nbsp;I approached him and said, 'Sir, I am a big fan of yours.' This was during the RCB vs Mumbai Indians game. He was very sweet. Back then we used to ask for bat or gloves from big players. But I was so shy, I could not ask for it!"&nbsp;</p>
<p>He added: "There was another incident. In one game, Irfan Pathan was fielding at long on and sat next to us. He asked us 'mazaa aa raha hai?' We said we loved talking to him. That experience stands out for me." &nbsp;</p></div>
							</div>
						</div></div>
						<div class="clear"></div>
					</div>
					<div class="clear"></div>
				</div>
<div class="brdr20 lowlighted" id="tie-lb-20250508190829" data-timeframe="20250508190829"><div class="comment-body-live " id="lb-1011774"><div class="A win today for the Punjab Kings could see them became the first team out of the 10 to qualify for the IPL 2025 playoffs. But for that, they need the rain Gods to relent. Right now, it looks very gloomy in Dharamsala.&amp;nbsp;\nAs former India cricketer Murali Karthik said in the pitch report: 'There's a bit of rain in the air. We have had a bit of a delay even to do the pitch report.'&amp;nbsp;\nJust look at the skies behind Marthik when he was doing the pitch report.\n&lt;img src=&quot;https:\/\/indianexpress.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/05\/MURALI-A-.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;800&quot; height=&quot;455&quot; \/&gt;" id="lbcontentbody"></div><div class="lvblg-box-shr">
