									<meta content="https://images.indianexpress.com/2019/11/ienewlogo3_new.png" itemprop="url">
									<meta content="125" itemprop="width">
									<meta content="26" itemprop="height">
								</span>
								<meta content="The Indian Express" itemprop="name">
							</span>
							<meta itemprop="mainEntityOfPage" content="https://indianexpress.com/article/sports/cricket/dc-vs-pbks-ipl-2025-live-cricket-score-playing-11-punjab-kings-delhi-capitals-today-match-updates-9989423/">
							<meta itemprop="dateModified" content="2025-05-08T17:44:03+05:30">
							<meta itemprop="headline" content="PBKS vs DC LIVE Score, IPL 2025: PBKS powered by Indian core">
							<meta itemprop="articleBody" content="Perennial under-performers in the IPL, Punjab Kings (previously Kings XI Punjab) have looked like the real deal this season under new captain Shreyas Iyer and coach Ricky Ponting.&nbsp;
The team has a strong Indian presence with Iyer complemented by the likes of Priyansh Arya, Prabhsimran Singh, Shashank Singh, Nehal Wadhera, Yuzvendra Chahal and Arshdeep Singh.&nbsp;
Former India cricketer-turned-analyst Ajay Jadeja, talking on JioHotstar after PBKS' victory over LSG in their previous IPL game,&nbsp; highlighted how Punjab Kings' long-term investment in their Indian core is finally paying off.&nbsp;
&ldquo;The key for Punjab Kings has been their Indian core. They've invested in players like Prabhsimran Singh for years&mdash;even back when Anil [Kumble] was involved. They waited patiently to see him deliver, and now he&rsquo;s started scoring runs consistently. Shreyas Iyer, the captain, has also been phenomenal. He&rsquo;s had a few low scores, but when he gets going, he takes the team to a commanding position," Jadeja said.&nbsp;
He went on to add: "Over the years, the team had a strong Australian presence&mdash;probably something the owners preferred&mdash;but this season, it&rsquo;s the Indian players who are making the real impact. There&rsquo;s a belief in the group from the very first game. They&rsquo;ve played as a unit, without relying on just big names. Everyone&rsquo;s contributing in their own way, and that&rsquo;s been the biggest strength of this side.&rdquo;">
							<div class="lvblg-box">
								<div class="heading-lvblg"><h2>PBKS vs DC LIVE Score, IPL 2025: PBKS powered by Indian core</h2></div><div class="body-lvblg"><p>Perennial under-performers in the IPL, Punjab Kings (previously Kings XI Punjab) have looked like the real deal this season under new captain Shreyas Iyer and coach Ricky Ponting.&nbsp;</p>
<p>The team has a strong Indian presence with Iyer complemented by the likes of Priyansh Arya, Prabhsimran Singh, Shashank Singh, Nehal Wadhera, Yuzvendra Chahal and Arshdeep Singh.&nbsp;</p>
<p>Former India cricketer-turned-analyst Ajay Jadeja, talking on JioHotstar after PBKS' victory over LSG in their previous IPL game,&nbsp; highlighted how Punjab Kings' long-term investment in their Indian core is finally paying off.&nbsp;</p>
<p>&ldquo;The key for Punjab Kings has been their Indian core. They've invested in players like Prabhsimran Singh for years&mdash;even back when Anil [Kumble] was involved. They waited patiently to see him deliver, and now he&rsquo;s started scoring runs consistently. Shreyas Iyer, the captain, has also been phenomenal. He&rsquo;s had a few low scores, but when he gets going, he takes the team to a commanding position," Jadeja said.&nbsp;</p>
<p>He went on to add: "Over the years, the team had a strong Australian presence&mdash;probably something the owners preferred&mdash;but this season, it&rsquo;s the Indian players who are making the real impact. There&rsquo;s a belief in the group from the very first game. They&rsquo;ve played as a unit, without relying on just big names. Everyone&rsquo;s contributing in their own way, and that&rsquo;s been the biggest strength of this side.&rdquo;</p></div>
							</div>
						</div></div>
						<div class="clear"></div>
					</div>
					<div class="clear"></div>
				</div>
<div class="brdr20 lowlighted" id="tie-lb-20250508172659" data-timeframe="20250508172659"><div class="comment-body-live " id="lb-1011769"><div class="In their last IPL 2025 game, Punjab Kings took down Lucknow Super Giants by 37 runs at the Himachal Pradesh Cricket Association Stadium in Dharamshala. That win could have significant ramifications on the playoffs, as former India cricketer Anil Kumble had explained right after that match.&amp;nbsp;\n&quot;One of those teams could go through on net run rate. So just having an extra point doesn&amp;rsquo;t guarantee anything&amp;mdash;you can&amp;rsquo;t afford to ignore net run rate. That&amp;rsquo;s why Punjab&amp;rsquo;s 37-run win was important. It&amp;rsquo;s still wide open,&amp;rdquo; Kumble had said on JioHotstar.&amp;nbsp;" id="lbcontentbody"></div><div class="lvblg-box-shr">
							<div class="ieo-datetime">
								<span>17:26 (IST)</span><span>08 May 2025</span></div>
