								<span itemtype="https://schema.org/ImageObject" itemscope="itemscope" itemprop="logo">
									<meta content="https://images.indianexpress.com/2019/11/ienewlogo3_new.png" itemprop="url">
									<meta content="125" itemprop="width">
									<meta content="26" itemprop="height">
								</span>
								<meta content="The Indian Express" itemprop="name">
							</span>
							<meta itemprop="mainEntityOfPage" content="https://indianexpress.com/article/sports/cricket/dc-vs-pbks-ipl-2025-live-cricket-score-playing-11-punjab-kings-delhi-capitals-today-match-updates-9989423/">
							<meta itemprop="dateModified" content="2025-05-08T16:25:31+05:30">
							<meta itemprop="headline" content="PBKS vs DC LIVE Score, IPL 2025: KKR could *STILL* make it to playoffs">
							<meta itemprop="articleBody" content="Kolkata Knight Riders' chances of making it to the IPL playoffs are almost over. But they do have a sliver of hope. Barely.
Aakash Chopra discussed KKR's slim yet persistent hopes of qualifying for the TATA IPL playoffs on JioHotstar after their loss to CSK yesterday.
"Never say never. Even with a 0.1% chance, it's not over yet. As improbable as it seems, if there's still a chance, you keep fighting. Sport teaches you to never give up," Chopra said while talking about KKR. "By the next game, others might be out of contention, but while hope remains, KKR will push for it. They face tough fixtures ahead&mdash;SRH away and RCB away. While SRH is near the bottom, they have match-winners, and RCB will be keen to finish the season with a double. KKR's game against RCB will be a crucial one."">
							<div class="lvblg-box">
								<div class="heading-lvblg"><h2>PBKS vs DC LIVE Score, IPL 2025: KKR could *STILL* make it to playoffs</h2></div><div class="body-lvblg"><p>Kolkata Knight Riders' chances of making it to the IPL playoffs are almost over. But they do have a sliver of hope. Barely.</p>
<p>Aakash Chopra discussed KKR's slim yet persistent hopes of qualifying for the TATA IPL playoffs on JioHotstar after their loss to CSK yesterday.</p>
<p>"Never say never. Even with a 0.1% chance, it's not over yet. As improbable as it seems, if there's still a chance, you keep fighting. Sport teaches you to never give up," Chopra said while talking about KKR. "By the next game, others might be out of contention, but while hope remains, KKR will push for it. They face tough fixtures ahead&mdash;SRH away and RCB away. While SRH is near the bottom, they have match-winners, and RCB will be keen to finish the season with a double. KKR's game against RCB will be a crucial one."</p></div>
							</div>
						</div></div>
						<div class="clear"></div>
					</div>
					<div class="clear"></div>
				</div>
<div class="brdr20 lowlighted" id="tie-lb-20250508162308" data-timeframe="20250508162308"><div class="comment-body-live " id="lb-1011767"><div class="Both Delhi Capitals and Punjab Kings come into this clash with playoffs on their mind, and in their sights.\nPunjab, under new captain Shreyas Iyer, have a slightly easier task at hand this season, since they have 15 points from 11 games while Delhi have 13 from the same amount of games.&amp;nbsp;" id="lbcontentbody"></div><div class="lvblg-box-shr">
