<div class="brdr20 lowlighted" id="tie-lb-20250508131658" data-timeframe="20250508131658"><div class="comment-body-live " id="lb-1011762"><div class="&lt;img src=&quot;https:\/\/images.indianexpress.com\/2025\/04\/Arshdeep-9.jpg?w=640&quot; alt=&quot;Arshdeep Singh Punjab Kings&quot; width=&quot;640&quot; height=&quot;360&quot; \/&gt;\nIndia and Punjab Kings pacer Arshdeep Singh said that as time has worn on and he has matured, he has taken the internet trolls and memes aimed at him in his stride, saying that now he just has a good laugh at them and gets entertained instead of getting irritated or annoyed.\n&amp;ldquo;I have had ups and downs in my career. I have seen the highest point as well as the lowest point in a very short span. But I feel very entertained by these trolls. I laugh at their creativity and memes. Earlier, I used to save these memes and messages so I could use those later but now I feel they don&amp;rsquo;t make any sense. However, I still enjoy looking at people&amp;rsquo;s creativity,&amp;rdquo; the pacer said in a &amp;lsquo;Kandid with Kings&amp;rsquo; episode.\nREAD MORE" id="lbcontentbody"></div><div class="lvblg-box-shr">
							<div class="ieo-datetime">
								<span>13:16 (IST)</span><span>08 May 2025</span></div>
