								<meta content="480" itemprop="width">
								<meta content="267" itemprop="height">
							</span>
							<span itemtype="https://schema.org/Organization" itemscope="itemscope" itemprop="publisher">
								<span itemtype="https://schema.org/ImageObject" itemscope="itemscope" itemprop="logo">
									<meta content="https://images.indianexpress.com/2019/11/ienewlogo3_new.png" itemprop="url">
									<meta content="125" itemprop="width">
									<meta content="26" itemprop="height">
								</span>
								<meta content="The Indian Express" itemprop="name">
							</span>
							<meta itemprop="mainEntityOfPage" content="https://indianexpress.com/article/sports/cricket/dc-vs-pbks-ipl-2025-live-cricket-score-playing-11-punjab-kings-delhi-capitals-today-match-updates-9989423/">
							<meta itemprop="dateModified" content="2025-05-08T13:16:58+05:30">
							<meta itemprop="headline" content="PBKS vs DC LIVE Score, IPL 2025: &lsquo;I laugh at their creativity and memes&rsquo;: Arshdeep Singh on how he deals with internet trolls">
							<meta itemprop="articleBody" content="
India and Punjab Kings pacer Arshdeep Singh said that as time has worn on and he has matured, he has taken the internet trolls and memes aimed at him in his stride, saying that now he just has a good laugh at them and gets entertained instead of getting irritated or annoyed.
&ldquo;I have had ups and downs in my career. I have seen the highest point as well as the lowest point in a very short span. But I feel very entertained by these trolls. I laugh at their creativity and memes. Earlier, I used to save these memes and messages so I could use those later but now I feel they don&rsquo;t make any sense. However, I still enjoy looking at people&rsquo;s creativity,&rdquo; the pacer said in a &lsquo;Kandid with Kings&rsquo; episode.
READ MORE">
							<div class="lvblg-box">
								<div class="heading-lvblg"><h2>PBKS vs DC LIVE Score, IPL 2025: ‘I laugh at their creativity and memes’: Arshdeep Singh on how he deals with internet trolls</h2></div><div class="body-lvblg"><p><img loading="lazy"  src="https://images.indianexpress.com/2025/04/Arshdeep-9.jpg?w=640" alt="Arshdeep Singh Punjab Kings" ></p>
<p>India and Punjab Kings pacer Arshdeep Singh said that as time has worn on and he has matured, he has taken the internet trolls and memes aimed at him in his stride, saying that now he just has a good laugh at them and gets entertained instead of getting irritated or annoyed.</p>
<p class="no_first_intro_para">&ldquo;I have had ups and downs in my career. I have seen the highest point as well as the lowest point in a very short span. But I feel very entertained by these trolls. I laugh at their creativity and memes. Earlier, I used to save these memes and messages so I could use those later but now I feel they don&rsquo;t make any sense. However, I still enjoy looking at people&rsquo;s creativity,&rdquo; the pacer said in a &lsquo;Kandid with Kings&rsquo; episode.</p>
<p class="no_first_intro_para"><a href="https://indianexpress.com/article/sports/ipl/arshdeep-singh-punjab-kings-growth-online-trolls-9949849/" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><strong>READ MORE</strong></a></p></div>
							</div>
